Verse 1:
Everyone has a bomb in their mind
And when it explodes
Blows your mind
After it all you'll wonder why
Sit back and look at you and I

Chorus:
Hasn't it been nice? Paradise?
Livin' lovin' life
What ya doin'?
To me?

Verse 2:
Some dawn we will wake up all mankind
And the outcome will shake up
The solitary mind
Some may look and some may see
What life has meant to you and me

Verse 3:
We've been hitchin' a ride all our lives
Just a-bumbin' a ride all our lives
Through the streets of have and hold
The morals new but the story's been told
